      "notes": "Born from late-night Twitter archaeology. Core insight: Adam's relationship to Brunswick tells the whole story \u2014 from 'Mordor' escape to city-dweller looking north. The Foursquare era (2010-2013) is richly documented. The quiet years (2013-2019) are the most interesting gap. Heraclitus: 'You cannot step into the same river twice.'",
